title: Economic Well-Being
subtitle: What Money Really Provides
new-page: true

Facilyn: Economic well-being is essential for meeting basic human needs - food, clothing, shelter, health, and security. But here's the key insight: focus on what money provides, not money itself.

Facilyn: "Making a lot of money" is rarely as useful in a quality of life statement as naming what you gain from having money.

What aspect of economic well-being matters most to you?

- #economic_aspects

